Connecticut Lake Profile Data

Wononscopomuc (Lakeville) Lake Report

Wononscopomuc (Lakeville) Lake is a 348.2 acre lake, located in the town of Salisbury within Litchfield County, Connecticut. The max measured depth of this lake is 32.9 meters. It has been sampled by CT DEEP Water Monitoring and Assessment on 16 sampling day(s) between 2016-05-19 and 2022-11-03.

The DEEP Water Monitoring Program conducts ambient monitoring and the related assessments of the State’s waters, including Connecticut’s many lakes and ponds. In Connecticut, there are a total of 2,267 lakes and ponds greater than 10 acres in size.

The Monitoring Program conducts annual monitoring on approximately 10-20 of these lakes and ponds per year. The type and locations of monitoring during a given year is determined by a variety of factors, including participation in regional and national studies, as well as support requests from groups within DEEP.
